  "texts": [
    "Becoming proficient in prompt engineering thus has an analogous meaning for a user of an LLM as becoming proficient in the Logo language for Papert's (1980) students.",
    "It not only allows one to make use of LLMs efficiently, but in order for it to work, i.e., to result in reliable and useful output, it entails practicing exactly that domain expertise which it presupposes.",
    "Given the necessary expertise, prompt engineering can thus become a form of playful interaction with LLMs, exploring various aspects of a topic by varying prompt patterns and techniques.",
    "Under those circumstances, the domain expert's intrinsic interest in the reliability and usefulness of results produced in cooperation with LLMs might provide some protection from over-reliance on a single output and associated risks of more narrowly directed LLM employments.",
    "However, such risks might be more severe for learners who are not yet domain experts but are presently on their way to developing such expertise."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}